com.palantir.giraffe.file.base

Class AbstractSeekableByteChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.palantir.giraffe.file.base.AbstractSeekableByteChannel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, ByteChannel, Channel, ReadableByteChannel, SeekableByteChannel, WritableByteChannel

    public abstract class AbstractSeekableByteChannel
extends Object
implements SeekableByteChannel
    An abstract base classe for SeekableByteChannel implementations.

    This class makes close() idempotent and provides utilities for managing the channel's position. All I/O operations are left to subclasses.

      • position

        protected long position
        This channel's position. While implementations may access this directly, they are encouraged to use advancePosition(int) and truncatePosition(long) when possible. This is exposed primarily for efficiency when reading the position or setting it to an exact value.

      • advancePosition

        protected final int advancePosition(int numBytes)
        Advances this channel's position by the given number of bytes, if it is positive. If the number of bytes is zero or negative, the position is not changed.
        Parameters:
        numBytes - the number of bytes transferred
        Returns:
        the input number of bytes

      • truncatePosition

        protected final boolean truncatePosition(long size)
        Sets this channel's position to size if it is less than the current position.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
